  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mobile Library for slum children in Trichy, India</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A survey says that only 32% of children read 24 out-of-syllabus-books annually in India.The project aims at envisaging the reading and educational opportunities for 1000 children and adults from 4 slums in Trichy. The mobile library (to start with in a two wheeler and 100 books we have) aims at providing weekly service to deepen the children&apos;s passion in reading. Children will have access to books &amp; Games (like carom, checkers, chess, etc.) that develop the thinking abilities and life skills.</narrative>
  </description>
